<p>Waow. I've just discovered <a class="sidelist" href="http://www.aneventapart.com/news/2006/11/an_event_apart_2007.php" title="An Event Apart 2007 Boston">An Event Apart</a> through an ad on <a class="sidelist" href="http://www.alistapart.com/" title="A List Apart">A List Apart</a>. The list of speakers left me drooling with envy.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/stevekrug/">Steve Krug</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/cameronmoll/">Cameron Moll</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/andrewkirkpatrick/">Andrew Kirkpatrick</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/dancederholm/">Dan Cederholm</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/mollyholzschlag/">Molly Holzschlag</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/ethanmarcotte/">Ethan Marcotte</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/jasonsantamaria/">Jason Santa Maria</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/ericmeyer/">Eric Meyer</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aneventapart.com/speakers/jeffreyzeldman/">Jeffrey Zeldman</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Just to name the featured ones..</p>

<p>I think I would have treated myself to a trip to Boston if the dates were right. Unfortunately, March is a busy month for me which explains why I've never attended <a class="South by South-West conference" href="http://www.sxsw.com/" title="South by South-West">SxSW</a> either. Annual reports are published, websites are revamped and both my children have their birthdays. Wouldn't miss the latter for anything in the world.</p>

<p><a class="sidelist" href="http://www.vivabit.com/atmedia2007/" title="@media 2007 conference">@media 2007</a> registration will open soon. Hopefully I catch up with a few of them in London next June.</p>
